                <article>
                    <h2>-&nbsp;Historique &nbsp;-</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>2009: </li>
                        <li>
                            December 17th - Natus Vincere is formed with Zeus, markeloff, ceh9, Edward, and
                            starix.
                        </li>
                    </ul>


                    <ul>
                        <li>2010 :</li>
                        <li>March 8th - Natus Vincere win Intel Extreme Masters IV after beating Fnatic 2-0 in the
                            finals.</li>
                        <li>July 4th - Natus Vincere win ESWC 2010 after beating SK Gaming 2-1 in the finals.</li>
                        <li>October 3rd - Natus Vincere win WCG 2010 after beating mTw 2-1 in the finals.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>2011 :</li>
                        <li> March 5th - Natus Vincere win Intel Extreme Masters V after beating Frag eXecutors
                            2-0 in
                            the finals.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>

                        <li>2012 :</li>
                        <li>November 4th - Natus Vincere switch to Counter-Strike: Global Offensive.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2013 :</li>
                        <li>July 18th - markeloff leaves Natus Vincere to join Astana Dragons</li>
                        <li>July 19th - Edward leaves Natus Vincere to join Astana Dragons. </li>
                        <li>August 20th - Natus Vincere sign seized and kibaken to complete their roster.</li>
                        <li>December 9th - Natus Vincere replace kibaken and ceh9 with GuardiaN and Edward.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2015 :</li>
                        <li>March 17th - starix steps down from the active lineup to become Natus Vincere's coach and
                            team manager; flamie joins as a stand-in. </li>
                        <li>April 10th - Natus Vincere sign flamie on a permanent basis. </li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2016 :</li>
                        <li>August 4th - Natus Vincere acquire s1mple from Team Liquid and bench Zeus. </li>
                        <li>October 12th - Zeus is acquired by Gambit Gaming.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2017 :</li>
                        <li>March 10th - After being with Natus Vincere for seven years, starix leaves the team after
                            many internal discussions. The team's analyst, Andi, takes over as coach.</li>
                        <li>July 28th - seized and GuardiaN are placed on transfer list.</li>
                        <li>August 3rd - GuardiaN is transferred to FaZe Clan.</li>
                        <li>August 9th - Natus Vincere acquire Zeus and kane from Gambit Esports, the latter as the
                            team's coach. Additionally, seized returns to the active lineup.</li>
                        <li>October 17th - seized steps down from the active lineup.</li>
                        <li>November 6th - Natus Vincere acquire electronic from, and loan seized to, FlipSid3 Tactics.
                        </li>
                        <li>December 10th - s1mple signs a two-year contract extension with Natus Vincere, keeping him
                            tied to the organization until the end of 2019.</li>
                        <li>December 15th - Edward and flamie sign a two-year contract extension with Natus Vincere,
                            keeping them tied to the organization until the end of 2019. </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>2018 :</li>
                        <li>January 14th - seized's loan with FlipSid3 Tactics ends and he becomes a free agent.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2019 :</li>
                        <li>March 30th - B1ad3 joins Natus Vincere as the team's esports director.</li>
                        <li>May 29th - Natus Vincere acquire Boombl4 from, and loan Edward until the end of 2019 to,
                            Winstrike Team.</li>
                        <li>September 7th - Edward's loan with Winstrike Team ends and he returns to Natus Vincere's
                            bench.</li>
                        <li>September 14th - Zeus retires and kane steps down as coach.</li>
                        <li>September 20th - Natus Vincere sign GuardiaN; B1ad3 takes over as the team's Head Coach.
                        </li>
                        <li>December 31st - Edward leaves Natus Vincere as his contract expires.</li>
                    </ul>


                    <ul>
                        <li>2020 :</li>
                        <li>January 24th - Natus Vincere acquire Perfecto from Syman Gaming and bench GuardiaN.
                        </li>
                        <li>February 21st - xaoc joins Natus Vincere as the Chief Operating Officer.</li>
                        <li>November 5th - Natus Vincere sign Pradiggg as analyst.</li>
                        <li>December 20th - Natus Vincere promote B1T from Natus Vincere Junior and establish a six-man
                            roster.</li>
                        <li>December 26th - s1mple and electronic sign a two-year contract extension with Natus Vincere,
                            keeping them tied to the organization until the end of 2022.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul>
                        <li>2021 :</li>
                        <li>February 12th - GuardiaN's contract with Natus Vincere expires.</li>
                        <li>April 11th - Natus Vincere bench flamie and return to a traditional five-man roster.</li>
                        <li>September 16th - flamie becomes a free agent after his contract with Natus Vincere is
                            terminated.</li>
                        <li>November 7th - Natus Vincere win the PGL Major in Stockholm, defeating G2 Esports 2-0 in the
                            grand final.</li>
                    </ul>

